description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you a committed individual with a passion for empowering and enabling health professionals through intelligent information?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Health Informatics Department at the University Hospitals Birmingham (UHB) are seeking a passionate, enthusiastic and innovative Information Analyst to join their team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Following the development of an innovative Informatics tool, the successful candidate will be invited to join the department working in the Healthcare Evaluation Data (HED) team. HED is a fast growing and diverse team that includes web-developers, analysts, statisticians and business managers, focused on providing data-driven analytics to UHB and the wider NHS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will play a key role in providing comprehensive, efficient information and analytics services, focussed on clinical quality, operational efficiency, patient safety and financial opportunity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The daily role will involve using SQL server and other packages to analyse, visualise and manipulate data, supporting HED development and user queries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the Senior Intelligence Analyst, the successful applicant will be an enthusiastic individual with drive and commitment, who is motivated by achieving, empowering and informing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates invited to interview will be sent details of a short exercise to prepare in advance. Interviews may be held as a two-stage process, with successful applicants invited back for a second round.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is based at Yardley Court, Edgbaston but will initially be based remotely due to the current coronavirus restrictions. The post is currently offered on a 23 month fixed term basis in line with approved funding.&lt;/p&gt;
